OL,3,CInside Britain's Asylum Crisis -
OL,4,CTonight
OL,6,FWe travelled to Stanwell, once a
OL,7,Fcommunity that welcomed asylum seeker
OL,8,Ffamilies into their local hotel, now
OL,9,Fup in arms about the Home Office's
OL,10,Frecent decision to move the families
OL,11,Fout and single men in. We met Jane who
OL,12,Fruns a local florist and says she no
OL,13,Flonger feels safe walking around the
OL,14,Fvillage she loves because of the gangs
OL,15,Fof men hanging around on street
OL,16,Fcorners. Jane told us she won't leave
OL,17,Fher young female staff alone in the
OL,18,Fshop and there is a real sense of
OL,19,Funease in the community.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
