OL,3,CInside Britain's Asylum Crisis -
OL,4,CTonight
OL,6,FAs of June 2025 there were around
OL,7,F32,000 asylum seekers living in
OL,8,Fhotels. And while all of the main
OL,9,Fpolitical parties agree hotels are not
OL,10,Fthe right solution, what are the
OL,11,Falternatives? Well so called
OL,12,F"dispersal accommodation" which is
OL,13,Fbasically residential housing now
OL,14,Fprovides homes for around 60% of
OL,15,Faround the 100,000 asylum seekers
OL,16,Fseeking accommodation support in the
OL,17,FUK.
